                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13239603" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 16:28:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trivial patch to shut thrift down just before gossip/MS.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239607" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 16:32:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;should we just have it call drain() instead of partially reimplementing it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239629" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 16:56:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tried that, but it feels like it makes the logic for decom much less clear, and has a side effect that drain shuts the node down, which we don&apos;t want.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239648" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 17:10:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why don&apos;t we want that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239655" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 17:16:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Historically I think the reasoning is you may have packaging that automatically restarts the process, which is something you don&apos;t really want with decom, but isn&apos;t a huge problem for drain.  David apparently ran into this problem on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1483&quot; title=&quot;RejectedExecutionException thrown on decommissioned node&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1483&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1483&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239660" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 17:20:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;WFM then, +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239677" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 17:31:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
